        {
          "id": "86c25d22b01c_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4623",
          "text": "I’ve been watching the conversation about “the Singularity” — that historic moment when a transcendent artificial intelligence awakens and takes over the planet. For some reason, the evangelizers of this story seem to be mired in a deep hatred for their own bodies and corporeal existence.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 58,
              "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Technological_singularity",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 43,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 59,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 42,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "86c25d22b01c_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "c9a6",
          "text": "Ray Kurzweil, the principal advocate of singularity thinking, fills his body with pills every day to preserve it long enough for an upload to the digital Matrix. He can’t wait to shake off this mortal coil and achieve immortality by leaving all of his humanness behind. He idolizes machine intelligence and confuses it with the inherent intelligence of nature — the wellspring that makes digital computing possible.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 12,
              "href": "http://www.kurzweilai.net/",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 0,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "86c25d22b01c_5",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e065",
          "text": "But what if he has it exactly backwards?",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "86c25d22b01c_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "a0bf",
          "text": "",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "1*nKW2fnRxG1Vq3ACFko2CmA.png",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "OUTSET_LEFT",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "86c25d22b01c_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "cc4a",
          "text": "My studies of embodied cognition* tell a different story:",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 33,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 14,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "86c25d22b01c_8",
          "href": null,
          "name": "7e2d",
          "text": "The mind is an emergent pattern of body, brain, and situated environment. This is what the last half century of cognitive science tells us. We are the dynamic patterns of life that arise when primate bodies interact in social networks to create cultural realities.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "BQ"
        },
        {
          "id": "86c25d22b01c_9",
          "href": null,
          "name": "41ad",
          "text": "*Books on embodied cognition include The Embodied Mind, Embodiment and Cognitive Science, The Political Mind, Philosophy in the Flesh, The Meaning of the Body, Incomplete Nature, Self Comes to Mind, Louder Than Words, and many many more.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
